The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has denied media reports that its Presidential Candidate, Atiku Abubakar was flown to London, over health challenges. Spokesperson and Director, Public Affairs, PDP Presidential Campaign Management Committee, Dino Melaye, said this in a statement in Abuja. “Disregard the lies of unrepentant liars. Atiku is 100 per cent fit and in super form health wise. READ ALSO:“Atiku Is Dangerously Ill, Ran Abroad For Treatment” – Fani-Kayode “The British Government invited the leading presidential candidate, Abubakar, just like they had invited Bola Tinubu and Peter Obi earlier,” Dino said. Recall some media reports had stated that Abubakar was sick and flown from Dubai, United Arab Emirates to London, United Kingdom for treatment. 